text.tspan: QGP parameter extraction via a global analysis

flowRoot.flowPara: We conduct a systematic model-to-data comparison of an event-by-event hybrid model to experimental flow probability distributions.

text.tspan: H.-J. Drescher and Y. Nara, Phys. Rev. C 74, 044905 (2006).
H. Song and U. Heinz, Phys. Rev. C 77, 064901 (2008).
Z. Qiu and C. Shen, arXiv:1308.2182 [nucl-th].
S. Bass et. al., Prog. Part. Nucl. Phys. 41, 255 (1998); M. Bleicher et. al., J. Phys. G 25, 1859 (1999).

flowRoot.flowPara: A set of salient model parameters is chosen for calibration:
The model is evaluated at 256 points in parameter space. All parameters are varied simultaneously. Each parameter point requires at least 1000 events and 6 centrality classes.

text.tspan: Over 3.5 million events have been calculated.

flowRoot.flowPara: Average flow vn , width σn, and relative width σn/ vn for v2, v3, and v4 as a function of centrality (Npart). Colored curves represent model calculations; each plot contains 256 curves corresponding to the 256 points in parameter space.
Points are experimental data measured by the ATLAS Collaboration, JHEP 1311, 183 (2013). Error bars are systematic uncertainties.

text.tspan: Interpolation with a Gaussian process emulator

flowRoot.flowPara: Model output is interpolated with a Gaussian process emulator. The emulator provides fast predictions at arbitrary points in parameter space with quantitative uncertainty.
Shown here are emulator predictions of the centrality dependence of flow distribution parameters for several values of η/s. Other parameters are fixed at reasonable defaults.
Flow distribution parameters as a function of η/s in the 20-25% centrality bin (Npart ~ 200). Curves are emulator predictions at different values of Glauber parameter α and KLN parameter λ.
Dashed lines are the ATLAS measurement with systematic uncertainty represented by the grey bands.
